---
const stages = [
  {
    letter: "W",
    name: "Witness",
    tagline: "What was observed",
    detail: "Raw observations, each hashed with SHA-256 and carrying an optional custody chain. Content is retrievable either inline or via reference URL. Re-hashing retrieved content must reproduce the declared hash.",
  },
  {
    letter: "F",
    name: "Findings",
    tagline: "What was concluded",
    detail: "Claims derived from observations and prior claims. Each claim declares its inference type (observation, deduction, induction, abduction, compound), lists its supports explicitly, and enumerates its acknowledged gaps. Empty gaps on inferential claims are disallowed.",
  },
  {
    letter: "R",
    name: "Refutation",
    tagline: "What was challenged",
    detail: "Adversarial tests applied to findings — with outcomes. Beyond the challenges applied, a machine-readable inventory of challenges declined, each with its reason. The honest accounting of what was not attacked is required, not optional.",
  },
  {
    letter: "S",
    name: "Seal",
    tagline: "What was bound",
    detail: "An Ed25519 signature over the RFC 8785 canonical serialization of the three prior blocks. The issuer's public key is retrievable from a stable published URL. Any recipient can verify the chain end-to-end without the issuer's cooperation.",
  },
];
---
<section id="canon" class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24">
  <div class="section-label mb-4">§2 — The Canon</div>
  <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl leading-tight max-w-3xl">
    Four stages. One signed artifact.
  </h2>
  <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">
    A NORA Attestation is a JSON document produced when a claim has passed through four functions in sequence. The structure is public, implementation-neutral, and inspectable by any recipient without the issuer's cooperation.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-14 grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-px bg-ink-200 border border-ink-200">
    {stages.map((s) => (
      <div class="bg-white p-7">
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-3">
          <span class="font-serif text-5xl text-cardinal-600 leading-none">{s.letter}</span>
          <span class="font-serif text-xl text-ink-800">{s.name}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="font-mono text-xs text-ink-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">{s.tagline}</div>
        <p class="text-sm text-ink-600 leading-relaxed">{s.detail}</p>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 max-w-5xl">
    <div>
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink-800 mb-3">Canon specifies</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-600">
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-cardinal-600 font-mono">▸</span> JSON shape and required fields of every block</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-cardinal-600 font-mono">▸</span> Hash (SHA-256) and canonicalization (RFC 8785)</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-cardinal-600 font-mono">▸</span> Signature algorithm (Ed25519)</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-cardinal-600 font-mono">▸</span> Seven-step falsification protocol</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-cardinal-600 font-mono">▸</span> Inference-type vocabulary, versioning discipline</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-ink-800 mb-3">Canon does not specify</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-ink-600">
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-ink-400 font-mono">▸</span> Internal implementation of any stage</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-ink-400 font-mono">▸</span> Which challenge types are domain-required</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-ink-400 font-mono">▸</span> Storage or transport after issuance</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-ink-400 font-mono">▸</span> User interfaces for walking backward</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-ink-400 font-mono">▸</span> Choice of adversary models or key-storage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-14 bg-ink-50 border border-ink-200 p-8 max-w-3xl">
    <div class="font-mono text-xs text-cardinal-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Implementation-neutral</div>
    <p class="text-ink-700 leading-relaxed">
      Any implementation — NORA itself, a competing verifier, a recipient's own validator — may read or emit Attestations conforming to Canon without permission. The specification is dedicated to the public domain under CC0 1.0 Universal.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/NORA-BITSY/nora-canon/blob/main/CANON.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read CANON.md</a>
      <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/NORA-BITSY/nora-canon/blob/main/canon.schema.json" target="_blank" rel="noopener">JSON Schema</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
